<hack name="Purple Critter Parameters" author="Hina">
    <panel>
        <panel>
            <field type="info">
		For open eye/jump distances (basically how far the critter sees), 1 tile = 8192 units; the directions indicate where the player is coming from.
		Terminal velocity = maximum falling speed, please keep both values equal.
		In flying critters, maximum velocities come in pairs, please keep those equal to each other as well.
		</field>

           		 <field type="info">
				Purple critters shoot when their flight timer (a value that increases by 1 every frame until the flight time value is reached), divided by a predetermined dividend leaves a specific remainder - in other words, it's a modulo operation. You can change all the values in the fields underneath but you'll have to do the calculations on your own. By default, the flight timer is 60, the dividend is 30 and the remainder needed is 6, so the critter shoots twice, at timer values of 6 and 36. (because '6 % 30 = 6' and '36 % 30 = 6')
			</field>
